6. Orchestrator State
app/agents/orchestrator.py Analysis
States/Nodes in LangGraph:

Node Name	Type	Purpose
parse_intent	Function node	Keyword-based intent detection (create/approve/review/reject)
permission_check	Function node	Validates selected_agent_role against collection_agents
creator_agent	Async node	Creates content using RAG + LLM
reviewer_agent	Async node	Reviews content using RAG + LLM
approver_agent	Async node	Approves/rejects content using RAG + LLM
permission_blocked	Function node	Returns error message for denied access
Graph Flow:


Start → parse_intent → permission_check
                         |
        +----------------+----------------+
        |                                 |
(has_permission=False)        (has_permission=True)
        |                                 |
permission_blocked          → route to agent based on role
        |                                 |
        +----------------+----------------+
                         |
                        END
Permission Checks:

Location: permission_check_node() at line 94-118
Logic: Checks if selected_agent_role exists in collection_agents[selected_collection]
Router: permission_router() at line 281-299 routes based on has_permission flag
